<TITLE> Stocks slip for a third day </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, Nov 22 (bdnews24.com)  Stocks prices on the DSE declined for a third day Thursday in a row as small investors protested a Securities and Exchange Commission's decision to suspend loan disbursement by merchant banks and brokerage houses. DSE General Index (DGEN), DSE-20 Index and All-Share Price Index (DSI) declined 26.733 points, 23.247 points and 22.739 points to close at 2958.199, 2356.441 and 2504.189 respectively. Turnover hit Tk 1.42 billion on transactions of 9,590,915 shares. Losers beat gainers 146 to 50. Some 18 scripps held steady. Market bigwigs BRAC Bank, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh, Trust Bank, Islami Bank and UCBL led the gains. All the major indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also declined. Some 34 issues gained, 69 lost and 11 closed unchanged. bd
